-- Brazil's TIM hires Bradesco to explore bid for rival Oi, source says
-- By Guillermo Parra-Bernal
-- Fri Oct 03, 2014 02:47PM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, Oct 3 (Reuters) - Brazil's TIM Participações SA <TIMP3.SA> hired Banco Bradesco's <BBDC4.SA> investment banking unit to analyze a potential bid for rival Grupo Oi SA <OIBR3.SA>, a source with knowledge of the situation told Reuters on Friday.

TIM Participações, the Brazilian wireless carrier controlled by Telecom Italia SpA <TLIT.MI>, and Bradesco declined to comment.